Prepare a list of data frames to plot repulsive tags.

This function may be rarely necessary. Its input is a rare data structure. It is a list of dataframes, each corresponding to a 20x20 quadrat and with the variables: "tag", "lx", "ly", "subtag", "status", "symbol".

prep_repulsive_tags(df_list)

Arguments

df_list

A list of data frames.

Value

A list of dataframes, prepared for plot_repulsive_tags().

See also

Other functions to prepare data to plot repulsive tags.: add_latest_tree_status, add_limits_shrinked, add_limits, add_quadrat_and_subquadrat_from_list, add_quadrat_to_df_list, add_quadrat_to_one_df, add_subquadrat, identify_subquadrat

Examples

# The sinharaja package is local and the data set sinh_q20 is private.
# Choosing only two 20x20 quadrats
list_of_dataframes <- sinharaja::sinh_q20[1:2]
str(list_of_dataframes)
